"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707304","Home Office","false","2017-03-30","<p>The Home Office does not send letters to European Economic Area (EEA) nationals instructing them to make preparations to leave the UK. The refusal letters notify them that, on our assessment of the evidence provided, we are unable to confirm that they have acquired permanent residence.</p><p>The Home Office also provides applicants with information on options available to them, for example, clear guidance on providing the necessary evidence to make a successful application in the future, and of their right of appeal.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-03-30T15:50:18.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707304/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707304/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707304/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-02","Immigration: EEA Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will change the text of EEA Permanent Residence refusal letters to remove the instruction to recipients to make preparations to leave the UK.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","66324"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707305","Cabinet Office","false","2017-03-07","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-03-07T14:20:15.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707305/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707305/answer","PQ66292 v.05 (002) (1).pdf","PQ66292 v.05 (002) (1).pdf","UKSA Response to PQ66292","UKSA Response to PQ66292","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707305/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-03-02","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people from each other EU country are resident in the UK; and how many of those people have the right to remain from each of those countries.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Turner","Isle of Wight","Mr Andrew Turner","66292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707306","Home Office","false","2017-03-07","<p>The independent Office for National Statistics (ONS) is responsible for the net migration statistics.</p><p>In line with best international practice the ONS includes international students in net migration calculations. International students who stay for longer than 12 months, like other migrants, have an impact on communities, infrastructure and services while they are here.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-03-07T16:44:58.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707306/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707306/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707306/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-02","Overseas Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will make an assessment of the feasibility of extracting figures on the number of international students from overall migration numbers.","false","Biography information for Christina Rees","Neath","Christina Rees","66313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707307","Home Office","false","2017-03-07","<p>The Government's Violence against Women and Girls (VAWG) Strategy, published on 8 March 2016, sets out the importance of meeting the needs of LGBT and BME victims and survivors of VAWG, who may experience additional barriers to accessing support.</p><p>We have committed increased funding of £80 million between 2016 and 2020 to protect women and girls from violence and we are supporting local areas to improve local commissioning through the publication of a new National Statement of Expectations and supporting commissioning guidance which captures the importance of identifying and addressing the needs of LGBT and BME victims.</p><p>We are also funding the charity Imkaan to build capacity in the BME women’s sector and Galop to run a dedicated national helpline to provide emotional and practical support for LGBT people experiencing domestic abuse.</p><p> </p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-03-07T16:35:52.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707307/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707307/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707307/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-02","Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent assessment she has made of the adequacy of provision of services for (a) BAME and (b) LGBT victims of domestic abuse.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","66300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707308","Home Office","false","2017-03-09","<p>There is no cap on the number of genuine international students. All those students who have a sufficient level of English, funds to maintain themselves, relevant qualifications and a genuine intention to study can do so. The Government has no plans to change this.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-03-09T18:06:12.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707308/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707308/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707308/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-02","Overseas Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what discussions she or officials of her Department have had regarding placing limitations on UK universities' ability to recruit international students to the UK.","false","Biography information for Christina Rees","Neath","Christina Rees","66301"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707309","Home Office","false","2017-03-09","<p>I am sorry but Her Majesty’s Passport Office does not hold the data requested.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-03-09T18:10:06.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707309/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707309/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707309/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-02","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 5 December 2016 to Question 54640, on passports, what the ethnic profile is of UK passport holders.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","66279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707310","Department for International Development","false","2017-03-08","<p>The number of contracts within the Department below the OJEU threshold is not held centrally, they are tracked and managed by individual country offices. The requested proportion cannot, therefore, be provided without incurring disproportionate cost.</p><p>For live contracts above the EU threshold, each contract has a Senior Responsible Owner. There are currently 640 Senior Responsible Owners for live programmes in DFID. The number of staff managed by the Senior Responsible Owner in relation to monitoring contracts varies. On average there will be at least eight staff members directly involved in the oversight of each contract. The amount of time each staff member will spend varies depending on the type of contract and how it is performing.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-03-08T16:44:17.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707310/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707310/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707310/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-03-02","Department for International Development: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 22 February 2017 to Question 65001, what proportion of live contracts held by her Department are the 450 live contracts above the EU threshold; what estimate she has made of the amount of staff time spent overseeing those contracts; how many Senior Responsible Owners there are for those contracts; and how many staff those Senior Responsible Owners  manage in relation to monitoring those contracts.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","66402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707311","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-07","<p>We will close down ageing and ineffective prisons, replacing them with buildings fit for today’s demands. HM Prison Berwyn opened at the end of February this year, with a capacity of around 2,100 places. In addition, we will build up to 10,000 further prison places on a ‘new for old’ basis.</p><p> </p><p>We have applied for planning permission to redevelop the sites at HMP Wellingborough and HMP/YOI Glen Parva.</p><p> </p><p>We are currently considering sites for new prison places and will set out plans shortly. No further decisions have been taken on prison closures.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-03-07T11:20:30.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707311/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707311/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707311/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-03-02","Prisons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what her plans are for the (a) building of new prisons and (b) closure of prisons constructed in the Victorian period; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","66414"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707312","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-28","<p>The illicit use of mobile phones undermines the safety and security of prison. We are taking urgent and decisive action to tackle this issue.</p><p> </p><p>Under measures introduced in August 2016 the National Offender Management Service is one of a number agencies that can apply for Telecommunications Restriction Orders at Court to block specific mobile phones being used in prisons. Each order may specify multiple phones. Since the commencement of the powers, more than 150 phones have been disconnected through use of these orders. Further breakdown of these figures cannot be disclosed because this could disrupt ongoing law enforcement activity.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-03-28T09:37:25.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707312/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707312/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707312/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-03-02","Prisons: Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many telecommunication restriction orders have been (a) applied for and (b) granted in each month since those orders were introduced.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","66331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707313","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-04","<p>A reply to the letter from the hon. Member for Sheffield, Heeley of 15 February 2017 was sent on 30 March 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has repeatedly made clear that it is committed to commencing section 67 of the Serious Crime Act 2015 and the new offence will come into effect on 3 April 2017.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-04-04T11:53:04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707313/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707313/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707313/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-03-02","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when she plans to reply to the letter from the hon. Member for Sheffield, Heeley of 15 February 2017 on section 67 of the Serious Crime Act 2015.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","66332"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707314","HM Treasury","false","2017-03-10","<p>The government has committed to exploring whether some form of “breathing space” would be a useful and viable addition to the current range of debt solutions available to consumers and creditors. Work is continuing on this review, and the government plans to provide an update in due course.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-03-10T10:43:14.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707314/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707314/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/707314/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-02","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when the Government plans to complete its review of a proposed breathing space scheme for families in debt.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","66342"
