"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706760","Department of Health","false","2017-03-06","<p>The Government has committed to having 1,000 Physicians Associates (PAs) available to work in general practice by 2020, contributing to a more flexible workforce skill mix and supporting general practitioners.</p><p>Health Education England is supporting professional development for the role by working with stakeholders to develop a career framework and professional identity for the profession.</p><p>At present qualified PAs are not subject to statutory regulation but the Faculty of Physician Associates, based at the Royal College of Physicians, administers a PA Managed Voluntary Register that has 319 registrants as at March 2017.</p><p>The Department is currently considering options for a consultation on the regulation of Physician Associates, which will be published in due course.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","66107 ; 66108","2017-03-06T17:43:44.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706760/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706760/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706760/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-01","Physician Associates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when the consultation on the role of physician associates announced in his keynote speech to the NHS Providers conference on 30 November 2016 will be launched.","false","Biography information for Anne Marie Morris","Newton Abbot","Anne Marie Morris","66109"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706761","Department of Health","false","2017-03-06","<p>No meetings have been held between the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions and Secretary of State for Health on this issue.</p><p>Discussions relating to this policy are ongoing at official level.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-03-06T17:40:46.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706761/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706761/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706761/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-01","Health Professions: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 28 February 2017 to Question 65346, on health professions: training, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions on the roll out of that training.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","66110"
