"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706098","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-03-16","<p>There has been a marked increase in popularity of the Pet Travel Scheme in GB. In 2014 APHA issued 80,274 new pet passports to their official veterinarians, 119,704 in 2015 and 95,449 in 2016.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-03-16T13:41:02.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706098/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706098/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706098/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-02-28","Pet Travel Scheme: Dogs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 7 February 2017 to Question 62238, on Pets: Imports, for what reasons the number of dogs reported as entering the UK non-commercially under the Pet Travel Scheme increased between 2015 and 2016.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","65885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706100","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-03-06","<p>The Government remains committed to making a decision on whether to develop a National Policy Statement for water supply infrastructure. We are still assessing the evidence to support this decision.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-03-06T12:29:10.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706100/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706100/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706100/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-02-28","Water Supply: National Policy Statements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether her Department remains committed to developing a National Policy Statement for water supply for infrastructure; what recent assessment she has made of the need for such a statement; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","65876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706101","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-03-08","<p>We ran a consultation between 20 December 2016 and 28 February 2017 on proposals to ban microbeads in cosmetics and personal care products. The consultation also sought to gather evidence on the extent of the environmental impacts of microplastics, including microbeads, found in other products. We are now reviewing the responses to the consultation and any new evidence will be used to inform future UK actions to protect the marine environment.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-03-08T12:17:02.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706101/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706101/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706101/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-02-28","Microplastics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps the Government is taking to reduce or eliminate microbeads in products that are not currently included within the scope of the proposed ban; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","65879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706102","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-07","<p>It is the longstanding policy of the UK to oppose the use of the death penalty in all circumstances as a matter of principle. We use every opportunity to call on Belarus to establish an immediate moratorium on the use of the death penalty, as a first step towards abolition. For example, the UK funded a landmark conference 'Abolition of the Death Penalty and Public Opinion' organised by the Council of Europe in co-operation with the Belarus Ministry of Foreign Affairs, in Minsk in December 2016.</p><p>Despite some positive developments, the overall human rights situation in Belarus remains marred by systematic violations. The last EU-Belarus Human Rights Dialogue took place in June 2016. The dialogue allowed for an extensive exchange of views on the situation of human rights both in Belarus and in the European Union. The next EU-Belarus Human Rights Dialogue will take place in June 2017<strong>.</strong></p><p>The British Government remains concerned about restrictions on the rights to freedom of expression and of association, particularly the freedom of the media, which remains severely limited. We continue to urge the Belarusian authorities to eliminate all obstacles to the exercise of a free and independent media, including through the registration of new media outlets and the accreditation of journalists.</p><p>The Government does not currently recognise any prisoners in Belarus as being political prisoners. The release of political prisoners in August 2015 was a welcome step. We continue to urge the Government of Belarus to reinstate the full civil and political rights of released political prisoners.</p><p> </p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson","65862 ; 65865 ; 65868","2017-03-07T15:21:49.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706102/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706102/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706102/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-28","Belarus: Press Freedom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the level of media freedom in Belarus; and what representations he has made to his Belarusian counterpart on the accreditation of journalists in that country.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","65867"
