"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706104","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-08","<p>​Some improvements were observed in the conduct of the September 2016 parliamentary elections in Belarus. Two opposition candidates were elected for the first time, but the elections remained a managed affair, key Office for Democratic Institutions and Human Rights (ODIHR) recommendations remain outstanding and a number of long-standing systemic shortcomings remain.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson","65880","2017-03-08T16:26:09.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706104/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706104/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706104/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-28","Belarus: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the fairness of the conduct of parliamentary elections in Belarus held in September 2016.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","65869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706105","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-06","<p>We welcome the release of Mr Petr Jasek, but remain concerned about the sentencing of Pastor Hassan Abduelraheem Kodi and Mr Abdulmonem Abdumawlla. Officials from our Embassy in Khartoum regularly raise this case with the Government of Sudan, most recently with the Director for Europe at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs on 25 February.</p><p>More widely, we remain concerned at the continued persecution of Christians in Sudan. We continue to raise the importance of freedom of religion or belief in our human rights dialogue with the Government of Sudan. We urge the government to uphold the commitment to religious freedom in the Interim Constitution of 2005.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-03-06T16:29:46.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706105/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706105/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706105/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-28","Sudan: Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his Sudanese counterpart on the imprisonment of Reverend Hassan Abduraheem, Petr Jašek and Abdulmonem Abdumawla.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","65874"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706106","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-08","<p>The UK is not a participant in the EU Mobility Partnership with Belarus and has not therefore made such an assessment.</p><p>The British Embassy Minsk, as chair of the EU-Belarus Consular Working Group, has engaged the Belarus Ministry of Foreign Affairs on the imposition by Russian authorities of border controls between Belarus and Russia. The Ministry have told us that this is a matter for the Russian authorities. The Belarusian authorities are content for all nationals to travel in/out of Belarus provided that they have the correct visas.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson","65864","2017-03-08T17:06:18.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706106/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706106/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706106/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-28","Belarus: Russia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Belarusian counterpart on the imposition by Russian authorities of border controls between Belarus and Russia.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","65866"
